    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "10e93910_fe8d1266",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/virtualscene/PosterSceneObject.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 79,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-07T06:13:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m wondering what would be the differences if we end up loading a small placeholder texture first (including getting the OpenGL texture handle with glGenTextures) in the material creation, or something, and then re-defining it with glTexImage2D once the real data comes in.\n\nIt might make things less complex overall, with an initial cost of doing more work in update():\n\n1. Cost: update() can dynamically adjust to the current size of the texture if it has changed.\n2. But that means it\u0027s more decoupled from the explicit renderer state, which is good IMO.\n3. We can still initialize the material and mesh in ::create.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 78,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 79,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "156c4f97f1b7435d40503df89cb6e05d70d6b93f",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
